messageBody:
These characters are located in both the "King Plus" and "King Plus Monospace" fonts that I designed. I have not used my "Kingsley" font in a long while so I can not guarantee that those characters are in there. They are located in characters not easily accessed by a normal US English keyboard. Most word processors have a function to insert special characters from a font and that is probably the easiest method for you to use.

Full disclosure - I modified the two "X" characters so that they could be written in one pen-stroke.

--- In Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com, "cossyrosario" <cossyrosario@...> wrote:
>
> These are four characters present in the Wikipedia Chart
> <http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/b6/Quickscript_alphabet\
> _revised_names.png> which I do not find in the Junior Script font. And
> apparently not in the King Script font either.
>
> I also don't find Eat, Age and Ash in the Junior Script font.
>
> What font, if any, contains them?
>
